      "id": 361497,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Propose a structure for a compound, C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>7</sub>ClO<sub>2</sub>, that has the following IR and <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectra:</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa1VYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--53cb4d790a8c8c765db9f7f60991aee7ef21c3c4/OChem_21_EC_046.jpg\" alt=\"The I R spectrum of a compound of molecular formula C 4 H 7 C l O 2 shows peaks at 2900 and 1750 wavenumbers as well as several peaks between 1500 and 700 wavenumbers. The proton N M R spectrum shows three signals, a doublet at 1.69, a singlet at 3.79, and a quartet at 4.41 p p m. The signals integrate as 3, 3, and 1 respectively.\">",
